%-------------------------------------------------------------
\section{Even/Odd Decomposition} 

\begin{frame}
\frametitle{Even/Odd Decomposition}

Decomposition in a sum of two signals with symmetry properties.
\begin{block}{Base Shape}
\[
x_k [n] =\left\{\begin{matrix}
    x_{even}= x_{even}[N-n] \\ 
x_{odd}=-x_{odd}[N-n] \\
x[n]= x_{even}[n]+x_{odd}[n]
\end{matrix}\right.
\]
\end{block}
Equivalent to a Linear System with 2 constraints and 2 variables, plus two constraints on the solutions: it is possible if and only if the resulting functions respect both symmetry constraints.
\end{frame}

\begin{frame}
\frametitle{Base Shape, Visualized.}
\end{frame}

\begin{frame}
\frametitle{Finding the Decomposition.}

Let us find the decomposition analytically and check constraints, thus prove by construction it is possible to build such signals.
\begin{block}{Even/Odd Decomposition}
    Even/Odd decomposition $x_k [n]$ is such that:
\[
x_k [n] =\left\{\begin{matrix}
    x_{even}= x_{even}[N-n] \\ 
x_{odd}=-x_{odd}[N-n] \\
x[n]= x_{even}[n]+x_{odd}[n]
\end{matrix}\right.
\]
Let us find the values of $x_{even} and x_{odd}$: 
\[
\left\{\begin{matrix}
    x_{even}= \frac{x[n] +x[N-n]}{2}\\ 
x_{odd}=\frac{x[n] -x[N-n]}{2} 
\end{matrix}\right.
\]

\end{block}
\end{frame}

\begin{frame}
\frametitle{Java Code}
\end{frame}
